        <body>       
                
                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>Jewish Theological Seminary Association.<lb/>
                All Communications to be addressed to the Secretary&#44;<lb/>
                NO. 237 Broadway&#44;<lb/></p>
            <p>JOSEPH BLUMENTHAL&#44; President&#44;<lb/>
                DR. A. FRIEDENWALD&#44; V. President&#44;<lb/>
                NEWMAN COWEN&#44; Treasurer&#44;<lb/>
                JOSEPH E. NEWBURGER&#44; Secretary.					New York&#44; Jany 6<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1887<lb/></p>
            <p>Rev S. Morais<lb/></p>
            <p>My dear Sir<lb/></p>
            <p>Your favor with Enclosures to<lb/> hand this A. M&#45;&#45;I saw Rev H. P. Mendes this afternoon<lb/> and he will call a meeting of the Advisory Board of<lb/> Ministers for next Monday at 4 o&#39;clock&#45;&#45;he promised<lb/> to write to you as to same&#45;&#45;I have not the address<lb/> of Dr Cardoza&#44; but will ascertain it&#44; and notify him<lb/> to come before your Board on Monday&#44; and to avoid<lb/> any possible delay should Rev Mendes not write to<lb/> you <hi rend="underline">at once</hi>.  I will also drop a line to Rev Drachman<lb/> &#38; Mr Engelman to appear on same day &#38;c&#45;&#45;<lb/></p>
            <p>I have not yet been able to procure a free pass or<lb/> mileage book&#45;&#45;the party I wish to see is out of the<lb/> city&#45;I shall not neglect it&#44; but do my best to<lb/> get it&#45;&#45;The names you mention will be looked<lb/> after&#44; and their support solicited&#45;&#45;If you desire to be<lb/> present at our next Trustee Meeting&#44; which I intended<lb/> to call for Sunday the 16<hi rend="sup">th</hi>&#44; and will let me know as<lb/> to same soon &#40;or on Monday next when you come here&#44;<lb/> will do&#41;.  I will change the date to Tuesday the<lb/> 18<hi rend="sup">th</hi> in the Evening&#45;&#45;this would enable you to be<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>present at the lesson of the Students on the afternoon<lb/> of same day&#45;&#45;We can however speak of all this<lb/> on Monday next&#44; if you shall then be here&#45;&#45;please<lb/> if convenient consult Dr Cohen as to this&#45;&#45;<lb/> Although probably you have already knowledge of same<lb/> I deem it my duty to inform you&#44; that the Advisory<lb/> Board has arranged for the classes for Tuesdays&#44; Thurs&#45;<lb/>days &#38; Sundays&#45;&#45;Deuteronomy with Grammar&#44; with Rev<lb/> Jacobs &#38; Drachman on alternate Sundays&#45;&#45;<lb/></p>
            <p>Isai&#45;&#45;with commentary &#38; Rashi with Rev De Sola Mendes<lb/> &#38; Wise on alternate Tuesdays&#45;&#45;Rev Kohut&#44; Mishna<lb/> &#38; Rev H. P. Mendes&#44; History &#38; Literature on alternate<lb/> Thursdays&#45;&#45;This afternoon Rev Kohut was in charge<lb/> of the class&#45;&#45;Everything will no doubt gradually get<lb/> in good shape.  Especially when you shall have a<lb/> regular system governing the Seminary and the<lb/> Preceptor &#38;c&#45;&#45;If you can let me know what<lb/> time &#38; where you will arrive here on Monday&#44; I<lb/> will try to meet you &#38; we can talk over matters<lb/> before your Ministers meeting&#45;&#45;otherwise I shall<lb/> certainly and at any rate see you at meeting&#45;&#45;<lb/></p>
            <p>very Sincerely Yours<lb/>
                Joseph Blumenthal<lb/>
                151 East 73<hi rend="sup">rd</hi> St<lb/>
                or on Monday&#45;&#45;92 Liberty St<lb/></p>
            </body>
